{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c0d557d4-4a6f-4b5d-a1d9-d8027f5a304b","content":"Here's what you need to change in your `.csproj`:\n\n**1. Replace `NUnit3TestAdapter` with the MTP runner extension:**\n```xml\n<!-- Remove -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"NUnit3TestAdapter\" Version=\"4.6.0\" />\n\n<!-- Add -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"NUnit.Extension.MicrosoftTestingPlatform\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n```\n\n**2. Enable the Microsoft Testing Platform runner:**\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**3. Keep** `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` — it's still needed for integration with `dotnet test`.\n\nAfter these changes, `dotnet test` will use Microsoft.Testing.Platform instead of VSTest. You can also run the test project directly as an executable (`./MyTests`), which is one of the key benefits of MTP.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"eef497e5-5584-4157-8674-febecb6945fa","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating an NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing infrastructure - I don't need to search any codebase for this. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge.\n\nKey changes needed:\n1. Update NUnit3TestAdapter to version 5.0+ (which supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform)\n2. Add `Microsoft.Testing.Platform` package or enable it via a property\n3. Update the project file with `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` or similar\n\n\n4. The NUnit team provides specific guidance on which extension package to use for the migration, and I should clarify whether Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk needs to be kept or updated as part of this transition.","outputTokens":727,"requestId":"703A:1CDC41:E0383FC:F666D10:69F2A7C8"},"id":"132876d2-ddd8-4070-a7b4-ad6197e31644","timestamp":"2026-04-30T00:52:38.830Z","parentId":"44d2109b-baf1-4011-b5